     VALUES ('BREWERY', 'rooster-fish-brewing', 'Rooster Fish Brewing', 'Roosterfish Brewing&rsquo;s history begins in 1990 when the Wildflower Caf&eacute; was founded by owner Doug Thayer.  A microbrewery was in the original plans for the business but was not feasible at the time due to the high cost of equipment and space.  The Wildflower Caf&eacute; had enormous success, which helped the inspiration for the Crooked Rooster Brewpub&rsquo;s opening in 1998, again founded by Doug Thayer.  Throughout the running of these side-by-side businesses, Doug always had brewing on his mind and began to experiment in 2002 with home brewing.  Receiving excellent feedback on his brews from several beer aficionados, Roosterfish Brewing&rsquo;s first official beer, Black Walnut Nut Brown Ale (now known as Original Nut Brown Al e) was unveiled at the Crooked Rooster and Wildflower Caf&eacute; in 2004.  This was shortly followed with the Butternut Pale Ale, now known as Dog Tooth Pale Ale.  The drastic name changes occurred because the originals were rejected due to &ldquo;implied ingredients&rdquo; that weren&rsquo;t actually present in the beers.', 1990,
