     VALUES ('BREWERY', 'schlossbrauerei-auhallertau', 'Schlossbrauerei Au-Hallertau', 'The Schlossbrauerei Au-Halltertau respects the tradition and heritage of quality traditional premium brewing. For more than 400 years the brewery has been taking care that the local traditional beers are supplied regionally as well as internationally.<br><br>It is no longer important how advanced we are and how much technical support we use during our daily processes. The most important aspect for us is that we keep our traditional heritage. As we know the saying &quot;New is not in comparison with the word better&quot;.<br><br>The Schlossbrauerei Au-Halltertau respects the tradition and heritage of quality traditional premium brewing. For more than 400 years the brewery has been taking care that the local traditional beers are supplied reg ionally as well as internationally. The first documented brew master was the royal court brew master named &quot;Schweiger&quot; in 1590. At that time the Noble Freiherr Baron von Thurn was the lord of the castle. He was the fourth noble lord since 990 a.d through 1281 a.d that ruled in Au Hallertau.<br><br>Since 1846 the Noble rulers and Baron Freiherren Beck von Peccoz have ruled and resided in the magnificent &quot;Moated Castle&quot; in Au i.d. Hallertau.<br><br>The noble family of Baron Freiherren Beck von Peccoz is still living in the castle an in the meantime it is the 6th generation.<br><br>At present Baron Freiherr Beck von Peccoz is making sure that the Castle Brewery stays a traditional brewery together with the necessary vision  into the future to create a sustainable traditional premium quality future.<br><br>Michael Baron Freiherr Beck von Peccoz&rsquo;s utmost desire is not to miss a successful sustainable future and at the same time to keep up the 6 generations of writing a successful historical event for the Castle brewery and it history.<br><br>The Brew Master Mr. Stefan Ebensperger is supporting the Baron with his highly qualified experience and skills. The necessary emotions and bindings towards a brewing heritage that has been passed down for generations is needed. Tradition is naturally one of the highest priorities for Mr. Ebensperger due to our traditional purity laws dating back to 1516 a.d therefore you can be assured that the quality is a premium Ger man and he says, &quot;It will also stay like that&quot;. Since 1516 the Bavarians have known how important the quality of the ingredients and the brewing process actually are. Beer was known during the Middle Ages as the same significant value as bread. As a part of the staple die, it was also germ free and full of healthy calories. During that time the average citizen spent a good 20 percent of their income on beer.<br><br>On the 23. April 1516 the Bavaria Duke Wilhelm IV. Executed and introduced the famous Bavarian Purity law into the Bavarian Parliament in Ingolstadt with the famous words: &quot;Just like beer in Summer an in winter as well as the county or province it is brewed or served&quot; Since that day it is prohibited to brew be', 1590,
      '+49 / 87 52 / 86 32 - 0', 'http://www.auer-bier.de/', 'Schlossbrugasse 2', '',
      'Au in der Hallertau', '', '84072', 'DE', '3154',
        '2011-12-13T00:06:52.875-0800', true);

