     VALUES ('BREWERY', 'scottish--newcastle-breweries', 'Scottish & Newcastle Breweries', 'Scottish &amp; Newcastle plc was a &quot;long alcoholic drinks&quot; (LADs) company with positions in 15 countries, including UK, France and Russia. It was headquartered in Edinburgh, Scotland, UK. In the last 20 years, S&amp;N expanded significantly from its home base to become an international business with beer volumes growing almost tenfold. It was listed on the London Stock Exchange and was once a constituent of the FTSE 100 Index but it was acquired jointly by Heineken and Carlsberg in April 2008, with the company''s assets being split between them. The trading name &quot;Scottish &amp; Newcastle UK&quot; continued to be used, until November 2009, to denote the UK trading operation of Heineken International until it was renamed &quot;H eineken UK&quot;. The Scottish &amp; Newcastle name lives on through the former &quot;S&amp;N Pub Enterprises&quot; leased pub division which has been renamed &quot;Scottish &amp; Newcastle Pub Company&quot;.', 1749,
