     VALUES ('BREWERY', 'utah-brewers-cooperative', 'Utah Brewers Cooperative', 'Wasatch Beers (Schirf Brewing Company) was formed when Greg Schirf found his way to Utah from Milwaukee, America&rsquo;s beer capital, only to discover that his newly adopted home state did not have a brewery of its own. Recognizing a need and an opportunity, he committed to rectify this situation. In 1986, Schirf opened the first brewery in the resort town of Park City and named his beers after the majestic Wasatch Mountains that rise just east of Salt Lake City. In July 1989, Schirf Brewing opened its new company headquarters and the first brew pub in Utah at the top of historic Main Street in Park City.<br><br>In fact, it was Schirf who proposed the bill to the Utah Legislature in 1988 that would make brew pubs legal in Utah. There are n ow more than 12 thriving brew pubs in the state thanks to Schirf and the bill''s sponsor, Senator Mike Demeitrick of Price, Utah.', 1986,
      '801-466-8855', 'http://www.utahbeers.com/', '1763 South 300 West', '',
      'Salt Lake City', 'Utah', '84115', 'US', '1318',
